   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Ambush Shard</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img title="Elden Ring Ambush Shard" src="/file/Elden-Ring/ambush_shard_sorcery_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="ambush shard sorcery elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Spell Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Night Sorceries" href="/Night+Sorceries" target="">Night Sorceries</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 13</td> 
     <td>Slots Used 1</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Strikes from behind with projectile fired from distance 
      </div> <br><img style="float: left;" title="Attributes Requirement" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attributes-required-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attributes required elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Requires 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a> 23 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>&nbsp;0 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a>&nbsp;0 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Ambush Shard</strong> is a&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceries" href="/Sorceries" target="">Sorcery</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Ambush Shard spell</strong> launches a projectile that strikes enemies from behind. Updated to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>One of the night sorceries of Sellia, Town of Sorcery.<br><br>Launches a projectile from a distance removed from the caster, so as to strike the enemy from behind.<br>This sorcery can be cast repeatedly.<br><br>The Sellian sorcerers were assassins, and it is said that they often hunted their fellows.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Ambush Shard Location in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p><strong>Ambush Shard</strong> can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li> <p><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weeping Peninsula" href="/Weeping+Peninsula" target="">Weeping Peninsula</a>: Found on a corpse in the underground jail of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Witchbane Ruins" href="/Witchbane+Ruins" target="">Witchbane Ruins</a>. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=6003&amp;lat=-212.359375&amp;lng=95.598058&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=6003&amp;lat=-212.359375&amp;lng=95.598058&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Interactive Map Link</a></p> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Ambush Shard Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Considered a&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Night Sorceries" href="/Night+Sorceries">Night Sorcery</a>. 
  <ul> 
   <li>Despite this however, the spells damage is not increased by a Staff of Loss.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Stamina Cost:&nbsp;15</li> 
 <li>This sorcery shoots a projectile from behind an enemy, making it useful for enemies with shields.</li> 
 <li>Due to the nature of Night Sorceries, enemies will not dodge Ambush Shards.</li> 
 <li>It is a viable strategy to use this against shield-bearing enemies, since the sorcery will always try to strike its target from behind.</li> 
 <li>This is one of a handful of unexpected things whose range is increased from wearing the Arrow's Reach Talisman.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff6600;">Note:</span> This Spell was changed with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a> as follows: 
  <ul> 
   <li>FP consumption has been reducied from 16 to 13.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
